    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context `{Funext}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (**\n     Quoting Wikipedia:\n\n     The Grothendieck construction is an auxiliary construction used\n     in the mathematical field of category theory.\n\n     Let\n\n<<\n     F : C \u2192 Set\n>>\n\n     be a functor from any small category to the category of sets.\n     The Grothendieck construct for [F] is the category [\u0393 F] whose\n     objects are pairs [(c, x)], where [c : C] is an object and [x : F\n     c] is an element, and for which the set [Hom (\u0393 F) (c1, x1) (c2,\n     x2)] is the set of morphisms [f : c1 \u2192 c2] in [C] such that\n     [F\u2081 f x1 = x2].  *)\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Variable C : PreCategory.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Variable F : Functor C set_cat.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Record Pair :=\n    {\n      c : C;\n      x : F c\n    }.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition issig_pair : { c : C | F c } <~> Pair.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "{c0 : C & (F _0 c0)%object} <~> Pair",
